      <p>A well-operated Lewiston dispensary generating $300,000-$500,000 in annual revenue is a realistic target for the first year of operation. After year one with an established customer base, $500,000-$800,000 is achievable depending on market conditions and competitive positioning. The Franco-American demographic tends to favor value formats—larger quantities of flower at lower price points—which can drive volume without premium pricing.</p>
